I don't think this is correct. It's changing the behaviour of existing code. And the new test you added 'ancestor with list elements has OR operator' is returning wrong result.

I think the code should be something like this:
  final String operator = booleanOperatorsQueue.poll();
  appendCondition(normalizedXpathBuilder, ctx.leafName().getText(), operator, comparisonValue);
  if (processingAncestorAxis) {
      appendCondition(normalizedAncestorPathBuilder, ctx.leafName().getText(), operator, comparisonValue);
  }

And change appendCondition method to take operator as argument:
  void appendCondition(StringBuilder currentNormalizedPathBuilder, String name, String operator, Object value);
